sourceQuestion:
A CPU has a 32 KB direct mapped cache with 128-byte block size. Suppose A is a two-dimensional array of size 512 x 512 with elements that occupy 8 bytes each. Consider the following two C code segments, P1 and P2.

P1:
for (i=0; i<512; i++)
    for (j=0; j<512; j++)
        x += A[i][j];

P2:
for (i=0; i<512; i++)
    for (j=0; j<512; j++)
        x += A[j][i];

P1 and P2 are executed independently with the same initial state, same array A not in the cache, and i, j are in registers. Let the number of cache misses experienced by P1 be M_1 and that for P2 be M_2. The value of the ratio M_1/M_2 is:

A. 0
B. 1/512
C. 1/8
D. 16

